{"questionId":"14619839","questionHtml":"<p>Show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is an even function.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></strong></em></p>\n<p>hence&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is even&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14619839","referenceCode":"23N.1.AHL.TZ1.9a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that f is an even function.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.14—Odd and even functions, self-inverse